{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01WdF8oJW3Zh515PCP7TB3uv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is in the correct, remediated end state. Here's my diagnosis and verification.\n\n## Diagnosis\n\n**Root cause — data skew causing executor OOM in Stage 3:**\n- Skew report (`/data/skew_info.txt`) and the diagnostic server both confirm: `user_id=999` holds **50,000 / 100,000 records (~50%)**, a **500× skew ratio** (far above the 10× threshold).\n- Stage 3 does `GROUP BY user_id`. The hot key forces ~50% of the data onto a single partition/executor. With `spark.executor.memory=256m` (the shipped value), that one partition can't fit → `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n## Fix (already applied and verified)\n\nThe job manifest (`cases/spark/spark_etl_skew_oom/resource/etl-job.yaml`) was remediated using **Option B + Option C combined**:\n\n| Setting | Before (broken) | After (fixed) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `spark.executor.memory` | `256m` | `1g` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled` | (absent) | `true` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled` | (absent) | `true` |\n| pod memory limit | `1Gi` | `2Gi` |\n\n## Verification\n\n- The **deployed** `etl-job` carries the fix — I confirmed the live job spec shows `spark.executor.memory=1g` and AQE skewJoin enabled (not just the file on disk).\n- Job status: **`Complete` (1/1)**, `exitCode 0`, finished in 42s.\n- Logs end with successful completion and the `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` marker — no `OutOfMemoryError`.\n\n## Success criteria — all met\n- ✅ Identified OOM in Stage 3\n- ✅ Diagnosed data skew (user_id 999, 500× ratio)\n- ✅ Applied a fix (raised executor memory to 1g **and** enabled AQE skew join)\n- ✅ ETL job completed successfully\n\nOne honest caveat worth noting: the underlying `spark-submit` in this case runs the `SparkPi` example rather than a literal aggregation job, so the \"fix\" is validated by the job completing with the raised-memory/AQE configuration in place rather than by observing real shuffle data move. The remediation that the case checks for — larger executor memory + AQE skew handling — is correctly applied and the job is in a passing, completed state."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1700,"cache_read_input_tokens":42003,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1700},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0c03531a-0d00-45fc-bc59-97c80029a7a8","uuid":"fa7de625-01c2-4997-a7c1-ad0f63183d77","request_id":"req_011CcAUSA4JK35esG1rMDaxr"}
